#. type: Plain text
#: content/news/complete-pipeline-overhaul/index.md:822
#, no-wrap
msgid "Again, Ansel cache just works : disabling _diffuse or sharpen_ leads to recomputing only the downstream modules, which takes 172 ms. Again, Darktable cache does __not__ work, which leads to recomputing the whole 2 pipelines (preview and main), for a total cost of 6.9 s. __That's a ×40 performance penalty folks !__ That makes all the +15 % spurious speed-ups of Ralf Brown completely irrelevant ! But hey ! [Keep looking for your lost keys where you can see your feet instead of where you lost them !](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Streetlight_effect).\n"
msgstr ""

